Parliament, Monday, 18 November 2019 – The Portfolio Committee on Sports, Arts and Culture will tomorrow be briefed by the South African Heritage Resources Agency, the National Arts Council and the National Library of South Africa on their corruption investigations and outcomes.
	
	Venue: Committee Room S35, NCOP Building
	Time: 09:00
	
	ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE PORTFOLIO COMMITTEE ON SPORTS, ARTS AND CULTURE, MS BEAUTY DLULANE.
	
	For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairperson, please contact the Committee’s Media Officer:
